@endpoint GET /2020-05-31/function
@desc Gets a list of all CloudFront functions in your Amazon Web Services account. You can optionally apply a filter to return only the functions that are in the specified stage, either DEVELOPMENT or LIVE. You can optionally specify the maximum number of items to receive in the response. If the total number of items in the list exceeds the maximum that you specify, or the default maximum, the response is paginated. To get the next page of items, send a subsequent request that specifies the NextMarker value from the current response as the Marker value in the subsequent request.
@optional {Marker: str, MaxItems: str, Stage: str}
@returns(200) {FunctionList: FunctionList?{NextMarker: str?, MaxItems: int, Quantity: int, Items: [FunctionSummary]?}}

@endpoint GET /2020-05-31/distribution/{DistributionId}/invalidation
